    <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p>In the first part of this <a href="/drupal/features-first">Drupal Features guide</a>, you learned why Features is a vital tool for Drupal site builders and developers. We then created a new Feature, which contained a Todo list content type. In this part, you will create a View to display the todo list in a block and add the View to the Feature by recreating it. Views are not the only thing you might add to a feature module. You can add a whole range of components, such as image presets, context and strongarm (for variables) to an existing feature.</p>
